    "title": "Right Triangles (Easy)",
    "body": "In a right triangle, the Pythagorean theorem links the legs a and b to the hypotenuse c: a² + b² = c². Recognizing common triples like 3-4-5 saves time.",
    "key_points": [
      "a² + b² = c² (c is the hypotenuse).",
      "The hypotenuse is the longest side.",
      "Memorize 3-4-5, 5-12-13, 8-15-17."
